snippet.textDisplay: Fun Fact #3: The "[blank] US Gallons" on the fuel cap is another aircraft thing. US FAA regulations starting around the 70's or 80's required all fuel caps to be labelled with the type of fuel that the airplane used, and the # of gallons it could take.  This came about after a few propeller airplanes accidentally got jet fuel put into their tanks (with the same kind of results you'd expect if you threw diesel into your gasoline car).

snippet.textDisplay:
Fun fact: those "Reset" buttons (@18:16) are Circuit Breakers (instead of Fuses). And yes, they're the same type used in aircraft. :-P
They range from ~$25 to $100 apiece (instead of about 20 cents apiece for a fuse). https://www.aircraftspruce.com/catalog/elpages/klixon7277.php
